Fibonacci
Aim:
The aim of the Fibonacci sequence is to generate a series where each number is the sum of the two preceding numbers.
It is used to model growth patterns and solve problems using recursion and dynamic programming.

Algorithm:
1. Read the value of n and validate n ≥ 0. 
2. Handle Base Cases: 
 If n = 0, display 0 and stop. 
 If n ≥ 1, display 0, 1. 
3. Initialize a = 0 and b = 1. 
4. Repeat for i from 2 to n: 
 Compute NextTerm = a + b. 
 Display NextTerm (to satisfy the "Series" requirement). 
 Update a = b and b = NextTerm. 
5. Identify b as the nth Fibonacci term. 

Program:

#include <stdio.h>
int fib(int n)
{
    if(n == 0)
    {
        return 0;
    }

    if(n == 1)
    {
        return 1;
    }
    return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2);
}
int main()
{
    int n, result;
    printf("enter the integer number:");
    scanf("%d", &n);
    if(n < 0)
    {
        printf("Invalid Number!!");
        return 0;
    }
    result = fib(n);
    printf("fibonacci nth term is %d", result);
}
